76 pages of mutant mayhem!

Wolverine and the X-Men battle Azazel in the afterlife! 'The Quest for Nightcrawler' is by Jason Aaron and Ed McGuinness!

Deadpool collides with Agent Preston's killer robot! By Brian Posehn, Gerry Duggan and Mike Hawthorne!

Featuring material first published in Amazing X-Men #4-5 and Deadpool #22-23.

description:
Zodgeball

Billy the 4th Grade Space Captain and his new friends 2nd Grader, Zeke and 5th Grader, Bruce defend earth in the Galactic Zodgeball Tournament.
name: Zodgeball

volume.name: The Adventures of a 4th Grade Space Captain

description: The King is dead, long live the King. In "Four Horseman" a power hungry Prince kills his father to steal the crown and kingdom. He knows the only thing that can stop him is the magic wielded by his father's most trusted confidant, the Good Witch of the Dead Lands. Hiding in her place of power, she has been discovered and uses her magic to summon four warriors from across time and space.
name: The Four Horsemen

description:
Sea of Faces

Chapter 08 of Avaiyo, Vol. 02

After centuries of slavery under the oppressive rule of the Tamiran Empire, the people of Xiltria were finally able to regain their freedom. It's been nearly eight years since the Era of Slavery, and the tides of peace are beginning to wash away. Subtle remnants of the exiled Tamiran Empire still live on and are starting to give way towards a new threat.

One such threat has been brought to the doorstep of Pegil Village. Helpless to defend themselves, they call out for help in hopes that someone will answer. With their pleas heard, Sekken and Iyo push forward into the depths of Daskin's Lair. Separated from each other, they must rely on their own skills to face the impending dangers.
name: Sea of Faces

description:
Baby's Sad Tank

Cryptozoologist Dr. Trent Headley has captured Baby, which has made Baby sad. So very sad. What is Dr. Headley's plan for the lil baby sea creature? And who is the final player to join our story?

By the end of the Thirties, with the world one step close to the most terrible war, three characters, seemingly with nothing in common, find themselves implicated in a complex intrigue which will push them to the very limits of sanity. In this second and final volume, every bit of madness will fall into the "right" place. Sinking deeper and deeper into darkness, Joe Colter, Max Conrad and Juliette Smith keep advancing on their private investigations to find out that hell becomes real all around them. The most insane secrets will be revealed with a blood & guts big bang party at the end.

"The Maw"

The moment of Zero is upon us. The answers to âWhat is the Zero moment?â are ready to be answered in this thrilling issue of Boy Zero. New evidence surfaces on The Boogeyman killings, drawing the eye of the police toward a new lead; while the children decide to take matters into their own hands. Boy Zero is an epic noir spanning decades and two separate murder mysteries. The cases are somehow connected and Detective Drekker must connect them before the killings begin again.
name: The Maw

description:
MR. JIGSAW in BEACH BALLOONS by Ron Fortier and Gary Kato. In the twilight of the Charlton era, many new features were introduced in their pages, including the beloved Man of a Thousand Parts named Mr. Jigsaw! The character has gone on to have a popular career in his own title and appears here in an all-new adventure!

NEVER HITCH A RIDE by Jack Keller. From the Charlton Garage roars a vintage tale from Hot Rods and Racing Cars #89 (February 1968). Clint Curtis learns that it's just as true then as now... beware of picking up rides with strangers! A special preview of the new ACE Comics title, Classic Hot Rods and Racing Car Comics!

THE CURE-ALL by Stephen Skeates, Howard Bender and Neil Vokes. What's a werewolf to do when looking for a depilatory in the wild west? Find one of those snake-oil peddlers, natch! But those old-fashioned remedies never work... Or do they? A lurid tale of lycanthropy presented by Mr. Bones!

THE GOLDEN PHARAOH by Joe Gill and Pat Boyette. Originally commissioned in 1967 by Charlton Comics, here is an unpublished epic scheduled for the final issue of an action title that was never released. Ambassador Christopher Smith and his able assistant learn of a nefarious plot to steal all the world's gold!

THE BARELY SENTIENTS by Mort Todd. During the height of Charlton Comics' reign of Action Stars, there was an uncanny super-team that appeared in the back of the Thunderbolt series... well, this ain't them! A satire of Charlton's off-beat beatnik super-heroes, The Sentinels.

THE SPOOKMAN by Roger McKenzie and Sandy Carruthers. Detective Mastrocelli is drawn deeper into the arcane nightmare world of The Spookman! Does such a being actually exist, or is he a figment of the detective's ever-increasing fevered brain? The more he learns, the more questions are posed about the fate of the mysterious Aaron Piper...

John H. Woodson High School is under the Fear Crow's control. Kain is doing his best to keep his fellow students and the faculty alive but it's not going well. Meanwhile, Zandalee has managed to avoid being ensnared but will she be able to help anyone?

Double-size penultimate issue!

Chopstick faces his grief and reconciles with the death of his friend, re-emerging into the world ready to complete his mission... but is he already too late to save Tracy?

Of Depressingly Low Toilette

Watch bob as he tries to reason with an insane giant robot that's destroyed half the city. witness bob as he tries to deal with his parents and is forced into getting job applications. Behold bob as his fearless janitor tries to superglue his apartment building back onto it's foundation. Gaze in wonder as we behold the giant robot's back story and find out the disturbing truth as to why the aliens are bothering everyone. See with your very eyes what lies ahead for ed's cafe. if all of this sounds like a complete circus- well, that's because... it is.
name: Of Depressingly Low Toilette

description:
Out-Sorcering

Dr. Muskiday is afraid he's getting fired, and he needs Dr. Leonard's help. But Dr. Leonard's oracle service has been outsorcered. Now it's no longer about keeping his job. It's about keeping his sanity.
name: Out-Sorcering

description:
We All Have Ghosts!

They are all connected. Within the 12 worlds, although time and space separate them, they are all one in some way. Granted, some of the worlds may seem "primitive" and others "advanced" by your standards, they are all born from the same place. Each world shares the same origin, however the choices those who inhabited those worlds have made, have either advanced or regressed their people. The book of three is a map in a sense. A written history of the choices those very different inhabitants have made. Isn't it odd, however, to see that although all those who inhabit these worlds are not at all related, the choices they have made are surprisingly similar. Doesn't it make you wonder how they are all connected? If each world was born from the same beginnings, then it would only make sense that each would "die" if one destroyed the first world all came from....
name: We All Have Ghosts!

description: Third book in the Havenhurst series: an unhappy homecoming.

Wine and Vines part 1 of 3

After the events of our first arc, the boys are at their wits end. After years of peaceful monster huntin', they've met a foe that's always one step ahead. Bad guys are poppin' up like weeds, but will Eustace lose all his friends pullin' 'em out?

Roots run deep in the south.
name: Wine and Vines Part 1 of 3

description: Vera, Booth, and Elanor are at odds about what to do next as Isaac tries to pinpoint Osrick's location. The Hex goes into lockdown and Faye finally meets her match.

Acquiesce: After Story

When government agencies come to archaeologist Laila McCarthy for assistance, they are unaware her knowledge of dangerous relics was gained first-hand. But ancient enemies remember her as Sumerian demon Lamashtu and the first vampire.

A brief interlude with Laila and Kimmy.
name: Acquiesce: After Story

description:
Bad Day

After years of imprisonment the greatest threat to planet Magos have risen from beneath the surface and has started rampaging again. The spot at which they break through is near Captain Tumo's guard outpost. Felix senses the disturbance and races to help his father, after standing no chance in that fight. Felix's father, Tumo orders Felix to go to Tellon city and warn the Prowlers so they can fight together.
name: Bad Day

description: Mary Elizabeth and Amanda's investigation intensifies and gets increasingly awkward as they confront the sheriff, who is also Mary Elizabeth's husband, who also might be evil. It happens.

Tied up. Threatened. Taken prisoner. Kim has never been in greater danger. Will she break? Or will she break free? This is where it all ends. This is the climactic showdown you've been waiting to see!

Up, Up and Away with the LOL Pups!

The sky's the limit and the LOL pups will take you there!

Anpan and Nemu are two magical stuffed pups set with the task of making you laugh out loud at their adventures and antics! Whether it's a downhill bike ride with Anise, exploring and getting lost in the backyard, or imagining wonderful fairy tales with Kana, they'll be sure to put a smile on your face.

Get ready, because shooper cuteness and fun await inside their fourth collection of comic strips.
name: Vol. 4: Enjoy Every Day

description:
End of Days

Thomas Simmons was working on an experimental suit his father built when an explosion occured that burned him alive. Miraculously surviving thanks to the very suit he was working on he then fought a beast and experienced excruciating pain when the suit that saved his life broke through his body, changing his appearance drastically. Cyborgs attacked in the name of a man who believes the suit to be his own and they brought Simmons to the man responsible for the explosion that ruined his life - Alvin Severnya!
name: End of Days

description:
Into the Abyss

Leon's Ark is trapped in the Cosmic Abyss and if Leon can't get them home soon BAD things will start to happen to everyone onboard. Unfortunately Noah holds the key to their return and he's wandering the ark with mayhem on his mind. Meanwhile back in the normal world Choop and Squatch try to convince Chief Bunny to stage a dangerous rescue mission and Raccoonicorn gathers a powerful ally as he plots his revenge.
name: Into the Abyss

description:
Back in her own magazine at last! Our scarlet-tressed occult detective returns in a new series of color adventures. In this issue, enjoy the classic second chapter of "Dark Passion," by Dennis Mallonee, Mark Beachum, and Tim Burgard.

Also in this issue, from the pages of Champions Vol. 2 #5, it'a the second appearance of Sylvia the Last Vampire.
After the Earth is destroyed, Lasha Trinity and her dog, Rover, are alone in space. And space is full of peril. Space pirates in particular can be quite troublesome.

The Young Gun

It's Ascendant's day and the streets of Fey are alive with revelry. Many from all corners of the city-state have come to catch a glimpse of the man most presume to be the next high king of Elutheria.

Where the lights are dim, however, deadly plots have been set into motion. A killer watches and waits for the perfect opportunity to strike and the only one who can stop him is a young boy, in over his head, wielding a "pop gun".

Read the final prologue issue of "The Sword is my Lady. The Lady is my Sword." as it introduces you to the precocious Shell Bala.
name: The Young Gun

volume.name: The Sword is My Lady. The Lady is My Sword.

description:
The Imperium: Part 4

The hunt is on! Zarran and the other slaves from the mines make a run for it, even as a Grunt tracking squad closes in on them. Doctor Murrell uses his technology to experiment on Alina. The results of the experiment yields some interesting results. Trovaar meets with his Cerebral advisers.
name: Imperium: Part 4

description:
Foundations and Appearances, Part 1

Cayoti and Selene meet at Pulchra Sentetia bank to discuss Selene's future. At the same time, the Torchbearers desperately hunt for the mysterious Nyx. Things go awry when Nyx leads the Torchbearers around Hyperia, finally stopping at Pulchra Sentetia bank.
name: Foundations and Appearances, Part 1

description:
The team is at each other's throats - who wants to be a criminal and who wants to be a villain?

Simon's blood is up and he's looking to settle some scores, both in and out of his jail cell.

Not everyone is walking away from this climactic final issue of Unmasked.
As society crumbles, an ill timed PR stunt backfires, putting our heroes in mortal danger. Meanwhile, Pendragon finds out that there's more to their current woes than meet the eye...

Hunter's moon part 1

The identity of the Wolfen is revealed and a new character joins the hunt, one which may be too skilled for even Virgin to handle.
name: Hunter's Moon Part 1

description: UDON's first Street Fighter V story! This special one-shot comic reveals the past of Charlie Nash, and sets up the fan-favorite character's new status quo. Expect appearances from Street Fighter mainstays like Guile, Chun-li, M.Bison, and more as the dual nature of Charlie Nash (AKA Agent Shadow) is explored.
name: HC

volume.name: Street Fighter V: The Life and Death(s) of Charlie Nash

description: The Alpha Gods stage an assault on a secret laboratory to save a young girl from an evil organization's clandestine schemes. Who is Nyssa? And what is her connection to the Alpha God's leader, Paladin? They pursue the evil Lester Cravely to Mount Ararat where he has discovered a portal that will help him restore the Nephilim and their fathers, the Grigori, to this world. Can our heroes stop him before he unleashes this ancient evil upon the world?
name: GN

description: Apama Volume 1 is a collection of issues 1 through 5 of the ongoing comic book series Apama the Undiscovered Animal. It features four complete stories: The Origin of Apama; his inaugural donnybrook with the landscaper-gone-to-seed known as the Lawnmower Man; the two-part tale of terror which brings our hero face-to-face with The Million Year Hunger; and wraps up with the first appearance of a the brown and tan avenger's pscho-delic nemesis, Regina!
name: Volume 1

description: A standalone story about monsters, city living, and ill-considered favors.

Awesome Possum is a natural science comic anthology collecting art from seven natural science illustrators. The anthology is a collection of short comics about the natural world. The other artists and I are all graduates of a natural science illustration program at the University of Washington. After a year's worth of hard work, we couldn't give it up. We had to keep sharing. The natural world is a wonderful place that deserves exploration. We wanted to show you some of our favorite views of the natural world.

The book is 54 pages of comics and illustrations. Seven artists contributed eleven stories: Alyssa Suzumura, Angela Boyle (that's me), EJ Landsman, Ellen Van Wyk, Hatfield Koerner, Jessica Heide, and Kami Koyamatsu. The cover is full color (with beautiful art by Marly Beyer). The interior pages (comics and illustrations) are in black and white.

The book includes the following comics:

What is it: Opossum or Possum

Secrets of Insect Diversity

The Ostrich (or is it an emu?)

Gray Fox

Narwhal: What's my tusk for?

Brooding: The Lives of Periodic Cicadas

Pitcher Plants: Lunch Time in Borneo

Bat Humor

Octopus vs. Human Eyeballs

Kropotkin

Cute or Deadly: Tapir Edition

Maria Sybila Merian

175page graphic novel for 99cents!

Perfect starting point for new readers.

Witness the fall and rise of Cassandra Trava and Mikki Valencia, see how they become The Queens Of Ruin in the complete 60pg action arc of The Second Siege Of Arlam Station, and delve deep into the history of City War with the emotional "Everything has an off switch".

This collected volume also contains 30pages of bonus material including sketchbook, previews, cover gallery, and all new headings and inserts.

99cents and you're in.
name: Volume Three

volume.name: City War: The Queens Of Ruin

description:
A mutated cybernetic boar searches for his place in the world. Looking for peace, Cy-boar usually finds only danger, and skull splitting action!

In MIND GAMES, Cy-boar is hunted to the ends of the earth by shadowy forces, but who are they and what do they want with him?

This book contains a complete story collecting Cy-Boar #7, 8, 9, & 10 in a combined volume!
name: Vol. 2

description: Five realms. Five princesses. Zero men. In the land of the Five Realms, the existence of men has long since been evaporated from the hearts and minds of women. Princess Bethany--ruler of Evanfar, the largest and most prominent kingdom, finds herself at the center of a vast conspiracy that could not only threaten her kingdombut also her life! Journey to a place where magic is abundant, unicorns and ferrets can command armies, and five women struggle to find balance and power--in an ever-changing fairy tale world!
name: Vol. 1

description: Robert has a job so soul crushing that his spirit dies and then comes back to haunt his family, friends, and his now spirit-less body.

A gamer handle instead of a real name. Thatâs all Dante can remember after waking up in a strange hotel in an online digital wasteland. Only his gaming skills and the help of a mysterious girl can get him out safely. But first they have to learn why they've been uploaded and escape deletion by their terrifying digital guards, the Weirloks.

From the mind of Brendan McCarthy, cocreator of Mad Max: Fury Road!

For fans of The Matrix, Total Recall, and The Prisoner!

Donât miss McCarthyâs Dream Gang, in current issues of Dark Horse Presents!
The comic is a satire about the baby-boomer generation and the art world. It is the story about the child prodigy Julie Desire who eclipses both Warhol and Basquiat in brilliance.

volume.name: Do Ducks go to Africa in Winter?

description:
Chapter One

In the closing days of World War II, a widowed housewife turned cropduster pilot struggles to rescue her teenage daughter from a band of escaping Nazi war criminals who crash their plane near her small Texas farm.
name: Chapter One

description:
Trial by Fire

Join a seasoned and bitter war veteran, a genius with a cybernetic body, a telepathic refugee princess from the Middle Kingdom, a Japanese juvenile delinquent who reflexively causes the laws of physics to break down around him, and mysterious entity known simply as Eve, as they seek to defend humanity.
name: Trial by Fire

description: A cyberpunk slice-of-life following two aging hackers-for-hire on a job to commandeer a space-based advertising platform.
Kane Kage returns to Earth and seeks refuge in an old church. Once inside, he undergoes confession with Jonah Kripke. Kane's origin begins...

volume.name: Hunter S. Thompson's Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas Limited Edition Preview

description: In 1666, Dutch trading ships have unwittingly brought the last great plague of London to its crowded streets. Thousands have died. The alchemist John Reinhardt devises a ritual to summon Azrael, the Angel of Death, and to render all of mankind immortal. He succeeds, if only for 60 seconds--long enough to save thousands from the terrible fire that ensues. But, he pays a terrible price. Forced to assume Azrael's mantle, Reinhardt serves a wrathful and nameless Goddess who creates and destroys worlds at a whim. And, the Earth's time has come. A cult of Goddess worship has overtaken the world and counts down to a spiritual unification. But, Reinhardt knows the truth. To save the human race, he defies Her will and journeys to Earth in search of Raven D'Arc--a young woman in New Orleans who believes his story, and the miracle he performed. Only she can help him to recreate the Deathless Minute and save the world. But, the Goddess will not rest. Her agents pursue them in a race against time as Raven is faced with the ultimate decision... Writer Kurt Amacker (Dead Souls, Cradle of Filth: The Curse of Venus Aversa) and artist J.C. Grande (Johnny Monster) present an urban fantasy epic that examines the role of faith and the burden of responsibility. The ritual is ready. The moment has arrived. What will you choose to believe?
name: Vol. 1

description: Natasha's a live-in housekeeper for the Italian billionaire Raffaele. Ever since delivering her from horrid circumstances four years earlier, Natasha's carried a torch for him. Not only is Raffaele completely oblivious to her secret feelings, but he then proposes that they become engaged for show! To keep the public from finding out about his precious little sister's hospitalization due to a nervous breakdown, he wants Natasha to help him attract the media's attention instead. And so begins an engagement that will last only as long as it takes for his little sister to recover!
name: Vol. 1

description: JFH has been called "Fast & Furious" (with martial arts instead of cars) meets "The Warriors." For those that didn't know, the definitive MMA action comic series was adapted from an original screenplay. Now, experience the FULL STORY ARC of JFH: Justice for Hire. This first-of-its-kind Graphic Screenplay contains a redux version of JFH issues 1-4, and transitions into the cinematic screenplay that would be issues 5-12. Finally, the beautiful chaos of the Retribution Industry collides with the spirit of the martial arts to bring you action like you've never seen before. Includes new artwork from JFH lead artist Antonio J. Rojo.

volume.name: JFH: Justice For Hire - Graphic Screenplay

description: In issue #1, a SEAL team 6 operator named Jep finds that demons are real on a mission in Abbottabad, Pakistan. With the help of Colonel Gabriel the Judges team starts to take form. Issue #2 coming soon.

Collects the complete Jughead's Time Police storyline epic!

Get ready for a wild ride through time! Jughead has been drafted into a time-traveling police force, tasked with keeping history from going haywire. Is Jughead the right kid for the job? Find out in this digital-only collection!

In 2013, it's not enough for a soldier to be faster and stronger, they have to be smarter. Spencer Cradle was created to be the world's smartest soldier, but was considered a failure. But when the next generation model goes rogue, it's up to Cradle to hunt him down.
name: GN

description: The herons are out for blood, and nobody is safe ... not even the great Manuchehr.

Team Assembly

An aspiring comic creator realises he's going to need some help in order to get his project done. Joining forces with the overly ambitious editor Mike and brilliant but lazy artist Fer, David soon learns that making comics is not as easy as it looks.
name: Team Assembly

description: A morbid young girl documents the dead and dying of the dark sci-fi metropolis Hope City. With a #scienceexperiment on the run, she sets her sight on cutting a bloody shortcut to the top and a take the "cake" from the Villains that have a choke hold on the city.

It is the year 1972. A savage murderer keeps a western Italian city in terror. Every morning a new slashed woman's body is found. An experienced detective, Claudio Morante, starts to investigate the case, which turns out to be more difficult than expected. Will he be able to stop the killer in time, when the . . . Night Screams for Mercy?

This homage to the Italian giallo genre is written by Hannu Kesola and illustrated by Jussi Piironen.

Well, it seems that everything is going to be...

Eric finally decides to ask classmate Eden out on a date. She says yes, but there's a slight problem. He's already made plans with his housemate (and sentient pool-of-water) Dice. Not wanting to let the opportunity pass him by, Eric comes up with a plan to have dinner with Eden and still keep his promise to Dice. Can Eric keep every one happy tonight?
Ramzey must fight off a gang looking to take control of her home, at the same time, a man comes to her with an unsavory offer.
name: Part 1

description:
Rancid Milk Presents is a "one-man anthology" that collects various strips, short stories, and artistic experiments that I've undertaken over my endeavors as a cartoonist.

The first issue includes adaptations of "Le Voyage Dans La Lune" and a traditional Japanese fairy tale. There's also a few gag strips and an adventure featuring McKenzie Jones: Law Hamster.
